 :tx/rationale "Create task: SOUND-SCHEMA: Schema migration backward-incompatibility guard. CONTEXT: schema.rs (4,864 LOC) supports schema evolution via transaction — adding new attributes. No guard for backward-incompatible changes: changing value type (Long→String) after data exists, changing cardinality (Many→One) after multi-valued data exists, changing resolution mode (Multi→LWW) after multi-valued conflicts exist. Schema is rebuilt from datoms (Schema::from_datoms) so the LATEST assertion wins via LWW. Existing datoms valid under old schema are not retroactively validated. RATIONALE: Schema evolution that silently invalidates existing data is a consistency violation. The fix is a validation pass after schema-affecting transactions. APPROACH: (1) After any transaction that modifies :db/valueType, :db/cardinality, or :db/resolution-mode, run schema_validate_existing(store, new_schema) that checks ALL datoms against the new schema. (2) If violations found, return Err(StoreError::SchemaIncompatibleMigration { violations: Vec<(EntityId, Attribute, String)> }). (3) The --force flag can bypass this check (documented audit trail via :tx/schema-override). (4) Test: create attribute :foo/bar with Long type, add data, change to String type, verify SchemaIncompatibleMigration error. (5) Test: --force bypass creates override datom. ACCEPTANCE: (A) Backward-incompatible schema changes are rejected by default. (B) --force allows them with audit trail. (C) Test covers type change, cardinality change, and resolution mode change. (D) No impact on forward-compatible changes (adding new attributes). FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/schema.rs, crates/braid-kernel/src/store.rs (transact). TRACES-TO: INV-SCHEMA-004 (schema validation), C3 (schema as data)."
